@Name Oxide Mixer is low supply because in general we don't want high supply of units that produce other units because the piles can get too big.
@SilentSlayers It never auto-concedes in turns after 1 unless there is a disconnect. If the player is connected and uses all their time every turn, it allows it by default. If you're disconnected then it will boot you after 1.5 turns. If there is a player doing that all the time then report them, but we don't wanna kick players just because they didn't act. In some cases (endgames etc.) it can be correct to take no action during a turn but also correct to spend time thinking. In blitz games, it's even more common.
@jeacaveo (#NeverBrowserer) It's never too late to change the model but Clash Royale's model is based around actual pay-to-win upgrades of the in-game units and that would never work in Prismata. Current plan is probably to release a premium "complete edition" and just discount it a lot during Steam sales etc.. I don't know when/if we will commission more skins. There were plans to but it doesn't seem like a good use of budget. We might make some more ourselves, I kinda like doing it. 🙂

